<mjml> <mj-head> <!-- Title and Date --> <mj-title>Off the Record - April 1, 2020</mj-title> <!-- Description --> <mj-preview>The Hotchkiss Record is proud to announce that we will be continuing to produce a weekly online newsletter throughout the rest of the spring semester. To celebrate the first few days of Hotchkiss Online High School (HOHS), we have put together a special April Fools issue. However, when we printed out the issues to distribute in Walker Auditorium, we discovered that no one was there. So, please enjoy this newsletter instead. Feel free to click “Continue Reading” buttons in the previews below, or visit the website directly here.</mj-preview> <mj-attributes> <mj-all font-family="'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif"></mj-all> <mj-text font-weight=400 font-size=16px color=#000000 line-height=24px font-family="'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif"></mj-text> </mj-attributes> <mj-style inline=inline> .body-section { -webkit-box-shadow: 1px 4px 11px 0px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15); -moz-box-shadow: 1px 4px 11px 0px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15); box-shadow: 1px 4px 11px 0px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15); } </mj-style> <mj-style inline=inline> .text-link { color: #5e6ebf } </mj-style> <mj-style inline=inline> .footer-link { color: #888888 } </mj-style> </mj-head> <mj-body background-color=#E7E7E7 width=600px> <!-- BODY CONTENT --> <mj-section full-width=full-width background-color=#02174c padding-bottom=0> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-image src=https://graphics.thehr.org/newsletter/offtherecord_dark.png alt align=center width=400px /> <mj-text color=#ffffff font-weight=bold align=center text-transform=uppercase font-size=16px letter-spacing=1px padding-top=30px> <!-- Date --> Wednesday, April 1, 2020 <br> <span style="color: #979797; font-weight: normal">-</span> </mj-text> <mj-text color=#17CBC4 align=center font-size=13px padding-top=0 font-weight=bold text-transform=uppercase letter-spacing=1px line-height=30px> Lakeville, CT </mj-text> <mj-text></mj-text> </mj-column> </mj-section> <mj-wrapper padding-top=0 padding-bottom=0 css-class=body-section> <!-- TEXT CONTENT --> <mj-section background-color=#ffffff padding-left=15px padding-right=15px> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=16px> The Hotchkiss Record is proud to announce that we will be continuing to produce a weekly online newsletter throughout the rest of the spring semester. To celebrate the first few days of Hotchkiss Online High School (HOHS), we have put together a special April Fools issue. However, when we printed out the issues to distribute in Walker Auditorium, we discovered that no one was there. So, please enjoy this newsletter instead. Feel free to click “Continue Reading” buttons in the previews below, or visit the website directly <a href=https://again.paperless.thehr.org/ >here</a>. <br><br> - <i>The Record Editorial Board</i> </mj-text> </mj-column> </mj-section> <!-- Start of an article preview --><mj-section full-width=full-width background-color=#ffffff padding-bottom=0> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-image src=https://again.paperless.thehr.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/almeidafrenchdraft1-820x615.jpg width=600px alt padding=0 href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=116"/> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- Start of text --><mj-section background-color=#ffffff padding-left=15px padding-right=15px> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=12px align=right padding-right=5px> <i>Mr. Almeida has been incredibly enthusiastic about this whole shebang.</i> </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-weight=bold font-size=20px> All Classes Taught in French Starting Fall 2021 </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-size=12px height=15px font-weight=bold> Kiki Henry ’22 </mj-text> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=16px> Last Friday, Mr. Craig Bradley’s puppy disclosed the headmaster’s plan to gradually move all classes to be taught exclusively in French. This initiative, along with the establishment of mandatory weekly woodshop classes and the replacement of the rice station in the Dining Hall with a crêpe stand, will be fully implemented by the opening of the next school year. </mj-text> <mj-button background-color=#202F5A align=center color=#ffffff font-size=17px font-weight=bold href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=116" width=300px> Continue Reading </mj-button> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- End of text--><!-- End of an article --><!-- Start of an article preview --><mj-section full-width=full-width background-color=#ffffff padding-bottom=0> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-image src=https://again.paperless.thehr.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/awpikjetvgpiwjestjgo-2020-820x547.jpg width=600px alt padding=0 href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=64"/> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- Start of text --><mj-section background-color=#ffffff padding-left=15px padding-right=15px> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=12px align=right padding-right=5px> <i>Don’t mind their armpits</i> </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-weight=bold font-size=20px> Sanders and Biden Drop Out & Endorse Ex-Royals </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-size=12px height=15px font-weight=bold> Isabel Su ’22 </mj-text> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=16px> The United States’ founding fathers may have fought for freedom from the British monarchy, but only a few years under the current president has united the Democratic frontrunners in the 2020 presidential election in a push to bring it back. On Wednesday, March 32, Bernie Sanders, Democratic senator from Vermont and Joe Biden, former Vice President, announced their sudden decisions to drop out from the race. Both have excitedly endorsed former Prince and Duke of Sussex, Harry Charles Albert David, and his American wife, Meghan Markle. </mj-text> <mj-button background-color=#202F5A align=center color=#ffffff font-size=17px font-weight=bold href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=64" width=300px> Continue Reading </mj-button> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- End of text--><!-- End of an article --><!-- Start of an article preview --><mj-section full-width=full-width background-color=#ffffff padding-bottom=0> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-image src=https://again.paperless.thehr.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Danaasitshouldbe-820x547.jpg width=600px alt padding=0 href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=118"/> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- Start of text --><mj-section background-color=#ffffff padding-left=15px padding-right=15px> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=12px align=right padding-right=5px> <i>Oh no</i> </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-weight=bold font-size=20px> Dana Boat Sinks, Boys Move onto Climbing Wall </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-size=12px height=15px font-weight=bold> Isabel Su ’22 </mj-text> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=16px> One of the great institutions of our school, the Dana Boat, is now gone, leaving a hole in our hearts and on campus. Days before spring break began, the proctors of Dana decided to take the Dana Boat out for a spin on beautiful Lake Wondskguo…bmoivmuc. However, when the Boat made it to the center of the lake, the proctors realized it was taking on water and beginning to sink. </mj-text> <mj-button background-color=#202F5A align=center color=#ffffff font-size=17px font-weight=bold href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=118" width=300px> Continue Reading </mj-button> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- End of text--><!-- End of an article --><!-- Start of an article preview --><mj-section full-width=full-width background-color=#ffffff padding-bottom=0> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-image src=https://again.paperless.thehr.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/prepwifi-820x656.jpg width=600px alt padding=0 href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=120"/> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- Start of text --><mj-section background-color=#ffffff padding-left=15px padding-right=15px> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=12px align=right padding-right=5px> <i>1047 hahaha get it because prep wifi goes out at 10:47? …I’ll let myself out, thank you very much.</i> </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-weight=bold font-size=20px> A Moment of Shame for a Senior With No Name </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-size=12px height=15px font-weight=bold> Sander Kuijs ’21 </mj-text> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=16px> It is no secret that many Prep and Lower Mid students turn to their older friends for Senior wifi, which allows them to access the internet at any time they like. However, in a shocking turn of events, it was revealed during lunchtime on Thursday, March 5 that a Senior has been using Prep wifi since the beginning of the second semester. Mr. Roger Wistar, director of the Annual Pick-the-Oscars Competition, revealed the information in an especially sombre article on the school website. </mj-text> <mj-button background-color=#202F5A align=center color=#ffffff font-size=17px font-weight=bold href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=120" width=300px> Continue Reading </mj-button> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- End of text--><!-- End of an article --><!-- Start of an article preview --><mj-section full-width=full-width background-color=#ffffff padding-bottom=0> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-image src=https://again.paperless.thehr.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/3ul0kl.jpg width=600px alt padding=0 href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=122"/> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- Start of text --><mj-section background-color=#ffffff padding-left=15px padding-right=15px> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=12px align=right padding-right=5px> <i>Some say that she is still saying “and and and” to this very day.</i> </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-weight=bold font-size=20px> Introducing &*%, Our New AI Writer </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-size=12px height=15px font-weight=bold> Tina Deng '21 </mj-text> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=16px> Since the founding of The Hotchkiss Record, we have prided ourselves in quickly adapting and leading in a constantly changing world. At this point in history, the rising trend of artificial intelligence is unstoppable. AI bots are, indubitably, able to be trained more efficiently than humans (and perhaps with better consistency in following our style sheets). Led by our calls to transform the industry of journalism and in particular, fake news, we have successfully developed our first AI writer in history. We sincerely take pride in &*%’s stability, creativity, coherence, insightfulness, and fluidity. Now, we are proud to present the debut of &*%, in which we allowed her complete artistic license. </mj-text> <mj-button background-color=#202F5A align=center color=#ffffff font-size=17px font-weight=bold href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=122" width=300px> Continue Reading </mj-button> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- End of text--><!-- End of an article --><!-- Start of an article preview --><mj-section full-width=full-width background-color=#ffffff padding-bottom=0> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-image src=https://again.paperless.thehr.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/shoutouts-820x1015.jpg width=600px alt padding=0 href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=124"/> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- Start of text --><mj-section background-color=#ffffff padding-left=15px padding-right=15px> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=12px align=right padding-right=5px> <i>IM BACK!!!!!!!!!!111!!!!!!!</i> </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-weight=bold font-size=20px> Submit Your Community Shoutouts! </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-size=12px height=15px font-weight=bold> Sydney Goldstein ’22 & Eric Jin ’22 </mj-text> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=16px> Dr. Arthur Gibb, predecessor of Mr. Steve McKibben, current dean of community life, introduced an excellent, valuable, and admirable tradition during the 2018-2019 school year: shoutouts for commendable behaviors among community members. The Record sees it of great import to continue this tradition, as it adds a heightened sense of unity among the thoughtful members of the Hotchkiss community who do splendid things on a daily basis. </mj-text> <mj-button background-color=#202F5A align=center color=#ffffff font-size=17px font-weight=bold href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=124" width=300px> Continue Reading </mj-button> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- End of text--><!-- End of an article --><!-- Start of an article preview --><mj-section full-width=full-width background-color=#ffffff padding-bottom=0> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-image src=https://again.paperless.thehr.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/4121585709550_.pic_hd.jpg-820x820.jpeg width=600px alt padding=0 href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=212"/> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- Start of text --><mj-section background-color=#ffffff padding-left=15px padding-right=15px> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=12px align=right padding-right=5px> <i>Zoom is like a zoo.</i> </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-weight=bold font-size=20px> Events Moved onto Zoom: Swim Tests and Senior Dinner </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-size=12px height=15px font-weight=bold> Sydney Goldstein ’22 & Eric Jin ’22 </mj-text> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=16px> It is currently an understandably hard time for the Class of 2020, but Hotchkiss spirits will prevail in the midst of COVID-19. With Marking Period four moving to online, some Senior students realized that they have unfinished business, the most urgent being the swim test – a graduation requirement for all students. Furthermore, to restore a sense of community in the midst of chaos, the School will continue the traditions of Community Dinners and the Annual Senior Dinner, though on Zoom. </mj-text> <mj-button background-color=#202F5A align=center color=#ffffff font-size=17px font-weight=bold href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=212" width=300px> Continue Reading </mj-button> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- End of text--><!-- End of an article --><!-- Start of an article preview --><mj-section full-width=full-width background-color=#ffffff padding-bottom=0> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-image src=https://again.paperless.thehr.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/best-bank-account-bonuses-for-july-2018-820x461.jpg width=600px alt padding=0 href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=128"/> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- Start of text --><mj-section background-color=#ffffff padding-left=15px padding-right=15px> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=12px align=right padding-right=5px> <i>hi idk what to put here</i> </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-weight=bold font-size=20px> The College Board is an Amazing Institution and Should Take all of Our Money </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-size=12px height=15px font-weight=bold> Charlotte Urquhart ’21 </mj-text> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=16px> Since its inception in 1899, the College Board has dedicated its time and resources to helping millions of students achieve their goals in higher education. It oversees AP (Advanced Placement) classes to help students receive college credit. AP classes are just like college classes, except that they are taught by high school teachers with a high school salary. So, how does the college board help students achieve the dream of getting a five on the AP exam? </mj-text> <mj-button background-color=#202F5A align=center color=#ffffff font-size=17px font-weight=bold href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=128" width=300px> Continue Reading </mj-button> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- End of text--><!-- End of an article --><!-- Start of an article preview --><mj-section full-width=full-width background-color=#ffffff padding-bottom=0> <mj-column width=100%> <!-- Thumbnail --> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- Start of text --><mj-section background-color=#ffffff padding-left=15px padding-right=15px> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=12px align=right padding-right=5px> <i></i> </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-weight=bold font-size=20px> Why Distance Learning is Superior to Regular School </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-size=12px height=15px font-weight=bold> Michael Zhang ’21 </mj-text> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=16px> The novel coronavirus has brought distance learning to schools across the world with much controversy. Many question the efficiency of such classes - how will teachers ensure the attention of students during lectures and discussions? Others question the morality of the learning style - how will underfunded schools prepare for online classes without the tools to do so? Well, all these criticisms of distance learning are both ridiculous and unfounded. Who cares about any of those problems when distance learning solves infinitesimally more issues? From remedying climate change to promoting mental health and fostering emotional awareness and romantic confidence, distance learning provides extensive benefits that outweigh any harms. </mj-text> <mj-button background-color=#202F5A align=center color=#ffffff font-size=17px font-weight=bold href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=210" width=300px> Continue Reading </mj-button> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- End of text--><!-- End of an article --><!-- Start of an article preview --><mj-section full-width=full-width background-color=#ffffff padding-bottom=0> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-image src=https://again.paperless.thehr.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/FullSizeRender-692x1100.jpeg width=600px alt padding=0 href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=134"/> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- Start of text --><mj-section background-color=#ffffff padding-left=15px padding-right=15px> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=12px align=right padding-right=5px> <i>You could be like Dom.</i> </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-weight=bold font-size=20px> Mumble Rap Classes Coming to Hotchkiss </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-size=12px height=15px font-weight=bold> Stephanie Ge ’22 </mj-text> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=16px> Are you stymied by lack of passion for your current classes? Desperate to try something new next year? Look no further, for Hotchkiss will be offering a brand-new music set of course next fallster in Mumble Rap. </mj-text> <mj-button background-color=#202F5A align=center color=#ffffff font-size=17px font-weight=bold href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=134" width=300px> Continue Reading </mj-button> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- End of text--><!-- End of an article --><!-- Start of an article preview --><mj-section full-width=full-width background-color=#ffffff padding-bottom=0> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-image src=https://again.paperless.thehr.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/aprilfoolsarts-1024x576.png width=600px alt padding=0 href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=130"/> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- Start of text --><mj-section background-color=#ffffff padding-left=15px padding-right=15px> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=12px align=right padding-right=5px> <i>Disclaimer: Although the image on the left far exceeds its counterpart in technique and creativity, the famous Arnolfini Wedding Portrait is in fact located on the right, and a replica by Jack McGlinn ’22 on the left. </i> </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-weight=bold font-size=20px> An In-Depth Look at Talents at Hotchkiss </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-size=12px height=15px font-weight=bold> Stephanie Ge ’22 & Yihan Ding ’22 </mj-text> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=16px> Theatre student Jack McGlinn ’22 has discovered a new outlet in the arts as he practices social distancing in his hometown of Seattle, Washington. As part of the practice of his craft, McGlinn has been working on reproducing the work of master artists and has produced an incredibly lifelike sketch of the Arnolfini Portrait by Netherlandish painter Jan van Eyck (pictured below). He attributes his impressively realistic rendering of the original painting to approximately five minutes of hard work with No. 2 mechanical pencils and sharpies and slight touches of Crayola to accentuate the colors. “I love [visual] art,” he said. “[Visual] art is fun.” </mj-text> <mj-button background-color=#202F5A align=center color=#ffffff font-size=17px font-weight=bold href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=130" width=300px> Continue Reading </mj-button> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- End of text--><!-- End of an article --><!-- Start of an article preview --><mj-section full-width=full-width background-color=#ffffff padding-bottom=0> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-image src=https://again.paperless.thehr.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Screenshot_20200329-221911_Instagram-820x1018.jpg width=600px alt padding=0 href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=140"/> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- Start of text --><mj-section background-color=#ffffff padding-left=15px padding-right=15px> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=12px align=right padding-right=5px> <i>Cooper Roh shows his commitment to non-athletics.</i> </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-weight=bold font-size=20px> AOI: Cooper Roh </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-size=12px height=15px font-weight=bold> Margo Donohue ’22 </mj-text> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=16px> Cooper Roh ’22 is a two year Lower Mid, captain of the Quizbowl team, and a strong supporter for Varsity non-athletes at Hotchkiss. Whether exercising his thumbs for the buzzer or practicing social distancing from the MAC, he shows consistent engagement in purely non-athletic activities at Hotchkiss. Aside from Quizbowl competitions, he can also be found on Fairfield Farm participating in FFEAT during the Fall and Spring seasons, picking potatoes, or simply laughing and reflecting with friends. Teammate Huck Whittemore ’22 said, “Cooper has more photos of historical figures hanging in his room than he has pieces of athletic clothing in his closet.” </mj-text> <mj-button background-color=#202F5A align=center color=#ffffff font-size=17px font-weight=bold href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=140" width=300px> Continue Reading </mj-button> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- End of text--><!-- End of an article --><!-- Start of an article preview --><mj-section full-width=full-width background-color=#ffffff padding-bottom=0> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-image src=https://again.paperless.thehr.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/gallaherjupiterdraft1-820x1025.jpg width=600px alt padding=0 href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=138"/> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- Start of text --><mj-section background-color=#ffffff padding-left=15px padding-right=15px> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=12px align=right padding-right=5px> <i>*not to scale</i> </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-weight=bold font-size=20px> Gallaher to Compete Against Teens From Uranus </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-size=12px height=15px font-weight=bold> Rachel Mokriski ’21 </mj-text> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=16px> This Saturday, Christian Gallaher ’22 will travel to Jupiter to compete in the first annual Interplanetary Crossfit Games, along with the first-, third-, and fourth-fittest teens on Earth. As a member of Winter Team Training, Gallaher has been working all season to prepare to face off against teens from across the solar system. He said, “One of the challenges is that I have no idea what my competition looks like. Usually, I’m familiar with who I’m competing against, but I’ve heard from astronomers that the teens at Saturn could be up to three times my size.” </mj-text> <mj-button background-color=#202F5A align=center color=#ffffff font-size=17px font-weight=bold href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=138" width=300px> Continue Reading </mj-button> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- End of text--><!-- End of an article --><!-- Start of an article preview --><mj-section full-width=full-width background-color=#ffffff padding-bottom=0> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-image src=https://again.paperless.thehr.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/nightgolf-draft-1-820x547.jpg width=600px alt padding=0 href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=136"/> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- Start of text --><mj-section background-color=#ffffff padding-left=15px padding-right=15px> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=12px align=right padding-right=5px> <i>This is totally how this co-curricular is going to look</i> </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-weight=bold font-size=20px> Night Golfing Is Now an Official Co-Curricular </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-size=12px height=15px font-weight=bold> Hannah Goldberg ’22 </mj-text> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=16px> To the demand of students across thousands of classes, Night-Golfing has been officially named as a co-curricular for the fall and spring seasons. Night-golfing is a more intense version of conventional golf that holds its practice from 8 pm to 10 pm on weekdays, and 8 pm to 11 pm on Saturdays. The flexibility of the games appeals to students – the games can vary among players and occasions. Despite this, the activity is not to be taken lightly. A seasoned night-golfer, who wishes to remain anonymous, explained, “It requires a much higher level of depth perception than regular golf. You also need a lot of guts, determination, as well as a desire to have fun and engage in the games. Some people just don’t have what it takes.” </mj-text> <mj-button background-color=#202F5A align=center color=#ffffff font-size=17px font-weight=bold href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=136" width=300px> Continue Reading </mj-button> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- End of text--><!-- End of an article --><!-- Start of an article preview --><mj-section full-width=full-width background-color=#ffffff padding-bottom=0> <mj-column width=100%> <!-- Thumbnail --> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- Start of text --><mj-section background-color=#ffffff padding-left=15px padding-right=15px> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=12px align=right padding-right=5px> <i></i> </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-weight=bold font-size=20px> Various Hotchkiss Funds Redirected to Boys Varsity Basketball </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-size=12px height=15px font-weight=bold> Rachel Mokriski ’21 </mj-text> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=16px> After careful consideration and much anticipation, the school has come to the final decision that the Boys Varsity Basketball team will receive new funding to honor their mind-blowingly successful season this past winter. </mj-text> <mj-button background-color=#202F5A align=center color=#ffffff font-size=17px font-weight=bold href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=214" width=300px> Continue Reading </mj-button> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- End of text--><!-- End of an article --><!-- Start of an article preview --><mj-section full-width=full-width background-color=#ffffff padding-bottom=0> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-image src=https://again.paperless.thehr.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/office-820x512.png width=600px alt padding=0 href="https://again.paperless.thehr.org/?p=34"/> </mj-column></mj-section><!-- Start of text --><mj-section background-color=#ffffff padding-left=15px padding-right=15px> <mj-column width=100%> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=12px align=right padding-right=5px> <i>Which team will you join?</i> </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-weight=bold font-size=20px> Your Taste in Office Characters Will Determine Which Hotchkiss Team You Should Join </mj-text> <mj-text color=#212b35 font-size=12px height=15px font-weight=bold> Rachel Mokriski ’21 </mj-text> <mj-text color=#637381 font-size=16px> Access the quiz below. </mj-text> <mj-button background-color=#202F5A align=center color=#ffffff font-size=17px font-weight=bold href="https://again.paperles